        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(telegram): preserve inbound text entities",
        "body": "## Summary\n- render Telegram inbound formatting entities as markdown before building the agent-facing body\n- preserve bold, italic, code, pre, strikethrough, underline, spoiler, and text_link entities using Telegram's original UTF-16 offsets\n- add helper and inbound-body regression coverage for formatted Telegram messages\n\n## Verification\n- pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 extensions/telegram/src/bot/body-helpers.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-context.body.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot/helpers.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-context.body.test.ts CHANGELOG.md\n- node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/telegram/src/bot/helpers.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-context.body.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot.create-telegram-bot.test.ts\n- git diff --check\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Telegram inbound formatting entities should be preserved in the agent-facing body by rendering bold, italic, code, pre, strikethrough, underline, spoiler, and text_link entities from Telegram UTF-16 offsets into Markdown before dispatch.\n- Real environment tested: GitHub Actions Mantis Telegram Desktop Proof workflow on Ubuntu/Blacksmith runner against PR head `26ca98e760f0`; native Telegram proof path with private QA enabled, plus local Node/vitest targeted helper coverage for `extensions/telegram/src/bot/body-helpers.ts` and `extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-context.body.ts`.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\n  1. `gh run view 26072521900 --json databaseId,name,conclusion,status,url,jobs`\n  2. GitHub Actions job `Run agentic native Telegram proof` in workflow run `26072521900` executed the native Telegram proof scenario selected by `mantis: telegram-visible-proof`.\n  3. `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/telegram/src/bot/helpers.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-context.body.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot.create-telegram-bot.test.ts`\n- Evidence after fix: Live